'Ah, there you are.' you whisper as you spot the creature.
> use bow on deer

> use bow on deer

As you were about to fire an arrow into the hind another arrows whistles past your ear and kills the deer stone-cold dead. Emerging from behind a tree is Much the Miller's son. He looks at you in surprise.

'Robin, I didn't see you there.' Much gasps, 'I nearly had your ear off.'

'Luckily for me that my ear and a deer have considerable differences in size.' you laugh.

'Sorry, Robin but I'm starving. My father is making ends meet and I thought I should contribute to the family table.' sighs Much.

'Very commendable, young man. However, if Guy of Gisbourne caught you poaching you would be sent to the Castle dungeon - and possibly executed.' you scold.

Suddenly a disturbance in the trees puts you both on guard. Guy of Gisbourne and a few of the Sheriff's men emerge from the undergrowth.

'What do we have here? A couple of poachers, I see. Perhaps the cold steel of the Executioner's axe will do its job well tomorrow.' smiles Guy.

As the Sheriff's men grab you and Much they lead you away to Nottingham Castle.

You are in a small cell.  A dirty room with a narrow slit letting in little light.
You can go west.
You can see Much.
> cut dead rabbit

