> use quarterstaff on john little

> use quarterstaff on john little
After a brief contact of staffs, John manages to knock you in to the water, soaking you to the skin.

'Again!' you shout over John's laughter. He helps you back on to the bridge.

However, in a short time you are sitting in the river dripping wet again.

'It looks like my little bird's feathers were in need of a good clean.' laughs John.

Reluctantly, you admit defeat and he helps you once again on to the bridge.

'What say you, John. Join my motley crew of outlaws, I could do with a tower of strength like yourself?' you ask.

'Thank you, Robin. I was actually looking for you anyway to join your merry troupe. To push a mightier thorn in to the Sheriff's side is a good reason to join you.' he smiles but drifts off in thought with sad eyes.

'Then it is done! Welcome John Little or should I say Little John.'

You both laugh and pat each other on the backs as you head for Greenwood.

Nottingham Fair

The Nottingham Fair is an annual event every year to allow traders from all over the county and beyond to come and sell their wares. With street entertainers and all day drinking who could resist.

Allen a Dale returns in haste to Greenwood and informs you of the archery contest being held at the fair.

'The first prize is a silver arrow, Robin. It sounds like the one you told us about that was stolen from your father around the time of his death.' says Allen.

You ponder on how the Sheriff had acquired the arrow. All you remember is that it was Herne's Arrow - a symbol of hope. You must get it back.

'I am going to win that contest, Allen and retrieve what belongs to me now. I know it to be a trap but it's important to me. What say you all? Fancy a visit to the Nottingham Fair?' you smile.

Your men all cheer and you head for the fair.

